Durban - A 27- year- old man has been sentenced to life imprisonment for raping his aunt who raised him. The rape took place in September  2015. The Newcastle Regional Court heard that the victim had chased her nephew out of her home because of his criminal activities. The court also heard that she had raised him from a young age. According to KZN police spokesman Colonel Thembeka Mbele, the accused had accosted his aunt while she was sleeping in her home in the Mathukuza area, Newcastle. "He repeatedly raped her, stabbed her multiple times, strangled her and robbed her of cash before fleeing," said Mbele. "The victim was taken to hospital in a critical a condition," added Mbele. The accused left the province after the incident. A case of rape and attempted murder was opened at Newcastle SAPS. Mbele said investigations led police to Boksburg prison, in Gauteng in April 2017. "The accused was arrested for murder and was an awaiting trial prisoner." Mbele he was taken to Newcastle to face the full might of law for his heinous deeds. "DNA samples also linked him to a murder case that he committed in Fernie area in the Mpumalanga province. The accused was incarcerated for the duration of the trial until his successful prosecution," He was sentenced to life imprisonment for rape and ten years imprisonment for attempted murder. Mbele said his murder trial was continuing. DAILY NEWS